{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "ColorGrade",
  "description": "Color Grade, decomposed into its tonal atoms in legacy order: node.gain (exposure) → node.saturation (luma-based) → node.hue_saturation (hue rotate only) → node.contrast (pivot 0.5) → node.colorize (tinted highlight/neutral masking) → node.mix (Lerp crossfade back over the source by `amount`) → node.clamp_texture (floor at 0, the legacy max(result,0)). Replaces the fused node.color_grade kernel — same math and chain order, every constant matched (Rec.709 luma, K-matrix HSV, smoothstep mask bounds). Each stage is now a reusable atom you can wire a driver into, drop, or reorder.",
